'''Uramachi Kofun''' (裏町古墳) was a {{ill|keyhole-shaped Kofun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in Nishitaga 1-chome, Taihaku-ku, Sendai, Miyagi Prefecture. Constructed during the {{ill|Middle Kofun period|ja|古墳時代中期|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (5th century), the mound was approximately 40 meters in length, surrounded by {{ill|fukiishi|ja|葺石|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and cylindrical haniwa. burial goods such as a bronze mirror, knife, and iron arrowheads were excavated from a {{ill|pit-style burial chamber|ja|竪穴式石室|1=Vertical Pit-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=竪穴式石室|4=zh|5=豎穴式石室|1=Vertical Pit-Style Stone Chamber|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The site was investigated in 1972 and 1973 before being destroyed in 1973.

