Uramachi Kofun was located at the base of the {{ill|Mikamine Hills|ja|三神峯丘陵|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, facing the southern part of the Sendai Plain. At the time of excavation, the site was within Tomizawa, Uramachi, Sendai City. However, after changes in the administrative district, it is now part of Nishitaga 1-chome, Taihaku-ku. The area was once dotted with small to medium-sized kofun, including Uramachi Kofun.

